I think it’s important to remember that cows don’t create carbon out of thin air. They take it from what they eat, which takes the carbon out of the air. We have a carbon problem from digging up the carbon buried underground.
The better question would be which industry uses less gasoline and oil per calorie of food.
I think the best way to eat for the environment is to eat local food so that your food doesn’t have to travel across the country to get to you.

snippet.textDisplay: Not all meat is raised on factory farms or in the burned down rain forest.  I work with farmers who dedicate their lives to raising and producing great meat and dairy in a way that is environmentally friendly.  It is taking place in the NYC watershed in upstate NY and the farmers here banded together 25 years ago to create a program that helps them be better farmers and protects the source of the drinking water for millions of NYC residents.  The animals living on these farms are treated with respect and I would argue have a better life than many people in the world.  I appreciate the work that you put into this video and I am not disputing your findings, other then to say that it is not correct to suggest that all livestock agriculture is bad for the animals and the environment.  @Mark Rober please come visit the NYC Watershed and I can give you a tour of these wonderful farms and show you some of the scientific work that is being done here to protect the largest unfiltered surface drinking water source in the USA.

snippet.textDisplay:
This whole video is full of lies. I no longer trust this channel. It is clearly a PR stunt to push this crap on people. It not only has an unhealthy amount of estrogen, but removing cholesterol from your diet, which is REQUIRED to produce testosterone, is exactly why men are falling apart these days, both physically and mentally.

Why do you think there has been such a massive push of these products on us? Take a guess.

Not to mention the lies about greenhouse gases from animals being unhealthy. Big corporations produce 90% of the pollution, and our personal, individual habits, while important, do not necessitate screwing up our biology. It’s not saving the planet. It’s saving corporations by distracting us from the real issue. What happened to talking about overpopulation? Oh right, need growing consumption to prop up these crooked industries.

Of course Bill Gates is also a social engineer and has done tons of shady stuff around the world with his foundation and screwed up education in the USA.

So many things wrong with this and Mark is either paid off or needs to look into this deeper.
